/formal-ai/assignees{/user}","branches_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/branches{/branch}","tags_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/tags","blobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/git/blobs{/sha}","git_tags_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/git/tags{/sha}","git_refs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/git/refs{/sha}","trees_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/git/trees{/sha}","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/statuses/{sha}","languages_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/languages","stargazers_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/stargazers","contributors_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/contributors","subscribers_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/subscribers","subscription_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/subscription","commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/commits{/sha}","git_commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/git/commits{/sha}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/comments{/number}","issue_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/comments{/number}","contents_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/contents/{+path}","compare_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/compare/{base}...{head}","merges_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/merges","archive_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/{archive_format}{/ref}","downloads_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/downloads","issues_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues{/number}","pulls_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/pulls{/number}","milestones_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/milestones{/number}","notifications_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/notifications{?since,all,participating}","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/labels{/name}","releases_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/releases{/id}","deployments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/deployments","created_at":"2026-05-12T10:09:02Z","updated_at":"2026-07-19T23:46:13Z","pushed_at":"2026-07-20T00:10:09Z","git_url":"git://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai.git","ssh_url":"git@github.com:link-assistant/formal-ai.git","clone_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai.git","svn_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai","homepage":"https://link-assistant.github.io/formal-ai/","size":301113,"stargazers_count":5,"watchers_count":5,"language":"Rust","has_issues":true,"has_projects":true,"has_downloads":true,"has_wiki":true,"has_pages":true,"has_discussions":false,"forks_count":2,"mirror_url":null,"archived":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":48,"license":{"key":"unlicense","name":"The Unlicense","spdx_id":"Unlicense","url":"https://api.github.com/licenses/unlicense","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTE1"},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"has_pull_requests":true,"pull_request_creation_policy":"all","topics":[],"visibility":"public","forks":2,"open_issues":48,"watchers":5,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":true,"maintain":true,"push":true,"triage":true,"pull":true}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/pulls/795","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/795","diff_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/795.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/795.patch","merged_at":"2026-07-19T14:22:59Z"},"body":"Closes #781.\n\nThe reported session failed with a bare `403 GET https://shopozz.ru/...` and stopped. The underlying gaps were larger than one blocked request: research stopped after a single search-and-fetch round, and there was no way to represent *what an answer has to satisfy*, so a compatibility question could only ever produce one recommendation rather than the options a buyer actually wants.\n\n## What is here\n\n**Option networks (`src/option_network.rs`).** A product-agnostic constraint/option engine. A network holds what the answer must supply, what each discovered candidate supplies, and every **minimal set** of candidates that jointly satisfies the requirement — so an option made of *two separate items* (a conversion adapter plus the part it adapts) is a first-class answer, not an afterthought. Options are listed **cheapest first**, with the provenance ladder (authentic → official-compatible → generic-compatible) only breaking ties. Arithmetic is fixed-point, so ranking is deterministic.\n\nIt is an associative links network rather than a scoring model: constraints and established facts are ordinary `world_model::Context` links, and the still-open part of a question is an ordinary `ContextDiff`. `links_notation()` projects the whole network, sources included.\n\nNothing in the module names a product domain. `the_same_engine_sources_a_subject_that_shares_no_vocabulary_with_the_issue` drives the identical engine with a darkroom enlarger lens mount and a m39→m42 conversion ring.\n\n**Reading evidence (`src/option_evidence.rs`).** Candidates and prices are read out of fetched page text. The constraints supply the units to look for — a constraint wanting `output_voltage` in `V` makes the page search for *a number followed by `V`* — so no attribute name is ever matched against prose and the same code reads a Russian spec sheet and an Indian listing. An attribute the page does not state is **left open** rather than guessed.\n\n**Deeper research.** The planner now deepens across rounds instead of stopping after one search and fetch, skipping sources already read.\n\n## Two things worth reviewing closely\n\n**The deepening trigger is deliberately conservative, and that is a considered trade.** Token coverage is a weak proxy for \"answered\", and how much of a question a page echoes varies by language — the same page shape leaves two aspects open in Hindi and none in English. My first rule (any proper subset of aspects open) regressed five tests by re-searching questions that were already answered. Deepening now requires **exactly one** open aspect of a question with at least three. The cost is that genuinely partial answers with two or more gaps are returned as-is; answering with what was found beats spending a round on a guess about what is missing.\n\n**A parsing bug this caught.** Acer's real part number `A13-045N2A` ends in `2A`, which read as a 2-ampere rating and made a genuine adapter look underpowered enough to drop out of the answer entirely. Numbers inside alphanumeric tokens are now not measurements — `a_digit_inside_a_part_number_is_not_read_as_a_measurement`.\n\n**An E2E check I added and then removed.** I asserted over the real transport that no source is fetched twice. It cannot work: the planner is stateless and re-derives from the transcript, so every traced request replays all prior tool calls and a repeated URL is indistinguishable from replayed history. The invariant is real but only observable at the planner level, where `a_source_already_read_is_not_read_again` covers it. The reasoning is recorded in the script so it does not get added back.\n\n## Testing\n\n- 24 unit tests across `issue_781`, `issue_781_option_network`, `issue_781_option_evidence`, including a whole-task test that assembles the complete option set from page text alone and asserts the cheapest answer is the two-item combination.\n- Full suite green locally: **1839 unit / 153 integration, 0 failures**. CI green on `030b63cf`.\n- Per-requirement trace in `docs/case-studies/issue-781/requirements.md` (R12–R20), each row naming the function and the test that evidences it.\n\nRegenerated the committed self-AST census, its Agent CLI session, and the self-healing case, and repointed the `looks_like_error` meta-function record: all are censuses of real source and went stale when `Progress` moved out of `planner.rs` into its own module to stay under the file-size gate.\n\n## Not done\n\nThe option network is exercised through its own tests and reads real page text, but it is **not yet wired into the agentic planner's answer path** — a live session does not yet return tiered, cheapest-first option lists. That wiring is the natural next step.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/795/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/795/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":28179282272,"node_id":"REFE_lADOSbOoU88AAAABJUHFts8AAAAGj525YA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/events/28179282272","actor":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"referenced","commit_id":"ceef695540b1ed01226d2987818d3607b502588b","commit_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/commits/ceef695540b1ed01226d2987818d3607b502588b","created_at":"2026-07-19T12:21:59Z","performed_via_github_app":null},{"id":28181140794,"node_id":"CE_lADOSbOoU88AAAABJUHFts8AAAAGj7oVOg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/events/28181140794","actor":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"closed","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2026-07-19T14:23:01Z","state_reason":null,"performed_via_github_app":null},{"id":28185070163,"node_id":"REE_lADOSbOoU88AAAABJUHFts8AAAAGj_YKUw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/events/28185070163","actor":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"reopened","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2026-07-19T18:26:52Z","state_reason":"reopened","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/comments/5016917806","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/781#issuecomment-5016917806","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/781","id":5016917806,"node_id":"IC_kwDOSbOoU88AAAABKwgXLg","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-07-19T18:36:54Z","updated_at":"2026-07-19T18:38:31Z","body":"<img width=\"1131\" height=\"565\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/da4f3259-8c3d-4cb6-87b9-045ecc3753e6\" />\n\nIt actually does not work, it stucks for long, and does not respond. Instead of doing multi turn actions to produce single message answers, we instead must split it to smaller actions, and provide explanations on each step, once all steps completed, we provide summary message.\n\nSee how current modern AIs do that as in log: https://gist.githubusercontent.com/konard/4fde72c1b78155ab4977c10e04d328d0/raw/bdab84a06254762c617f269ac71a9341c9b1ea5e/tmp-solution-draft-log-pr-1784470815451.txt.log.txt (also check other logs from https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/795 pull request).\n\nFor that specific task we must have full e2e test, that confirms multi-turn actions in all our agentic CLI tools like opencode, agent, claude, codex, \n\nAnd after more than minute of wait it ended up with:\n\n<img width=\"1131\" height=\"565\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d460445d-6430-47e9-89e5-53caf1b4c8e7\" />\n\nSo it looks like it became worse, not better.\n\nAlso error reporting does not provide additional data about full server logs during this conversation see https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/800\n\nI previously asked to do something similar to gh-upload-log tool we have at https://github.com/link-foundation/gh-upload-log\n\nSo we provide more context about actual reasoning, executed requests and so on.\n\nIn API/agentic mode we should be transparent with all our actions and execute them via the multi turn tool calls, before each tool call we need to explain why and what we do and so on.\n\nReasoning steps should provide useful data, not be too algorithmic/robotic and so on. Actual reasoning steps should be recursive in our links (associative) representation.\n\nAnd in server logs per dialog, we should be able to see exactly each action.\n\nIf we call internal tools that must be part of thinking process, where we also explain what happening, but we in API/agentic harness CLIs we should focus on using available tooling to provide familiar experience for the user.\n\nAlso when that task is split into smaller ones user sees real feedback and understanding what happening, it is bad idea to do thinking for more than 10 seconds per message. Better do smaller actions and turns collecting data, thinking again, planing, replaning and so on.\n\nWe should generalize our codebase as much as possible, reuse all the logic we have in the best possible and general way, so we produce single meta algorithm capable of producing algorithms and executing them to solve all questions, tasks and coding.","author_association":"MEMBER","pin":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/comments/5016917806/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"minimized":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/re